OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,442,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F441A1781273476
OL,3,CHouse arson and race-hate graffiti on
OL,4,C'much calmer' night of disorder
OL,6,FMr Henderson said Thursday night
OL,7,Fwitnessed a de-escalation of tensions.
OL,9,F"Our heightened presence in our local
OL,10,Fcommunities and engagement to de-
OL,11,Fescalate violence continued last
OL,12,Fnight," he said.
OL,14,F"Thankfully, the situation was much
OL,15,Fcalmer than we have seen in recent
OL,16,Fdays.
OL,18,F"Our policing operation will remain
OL,19,Fover the weekend to ensure public
OL,20,Forder is maintained."
OL,26,@qD@AOUtD@GO]vD@AOUzD@AOU|D@UO]
